properties.headline: HOLIDAY TRAFFIC 2020/21 - NSW TRAVEL HOTSPOTS Various roads
properties.otherAdvice:
Various roads throughout the state will be impacted by heavy traffic throughout the school holiday period, particularly from mid-December to early January and also at the end of January.

Holiday-makers and locals travelling in affected areas should plan ahead and travel outside of peak times to make their journey as smooth as possible.

On key dates, traffic delays are expected at:

HUNTER/NORTH COAST

  • New England Hwy/Pacific Hwy, Hexham
  • Nelson Bay Rd, Salt Ash
  • Pacific Hwy, Coffs Harbour
  • M1 Pacific Mwy, Tugun Bypass

SOUTH COAST

  • Princes Hwy at Albion Park Rail, Nowra, Milton, Ulladulla, Jervis Bay and Batemans Bay
  • Jervis Bay Rd, Jervis Bay
  • Kings Hwy, Batemans Bay
  • Kings Hwy, Braidwood (on Australia Day)

BLUE MOUNTAINS

  • Great Western Hwy, Blackheath

See the delayed predictions chart for estimated peak times/dates to help plan your journey, and always allow additional travel time to take into account unforeseen delays.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - Summer Holiday period - SHOALHAVEN Booderee Ave, Illowra Lane at Hyams Beach
properties.otherAdvice:
Changed traffic conditions including a new roundabout under traffic control at the intersection of Booderee Ave and Illowra Lane, and speed reductions will be in place to manage the heavy traffic over the busy period from 26 December to 27 January. 

A speed reduction from 80km/h to 40km/h will be in effect along Booderee Ave in both directions. 

If Hyams Beach reaches capacity, or in the event of a catastrophic fire danger rating, temporary closures at Booderee Ave may be implemented.

Motorists should arrive early or expect significant delays on roads approaching the township and beach during this period.  

Alternative white sand beaches can be found at Shoalhaven – South Coast NSW.

The Queensland state government has imposed restrictions at the NSW-QLD border as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

Border control measures can change quickly with people intending to travel from NSW to Queensland advised to visit the covid19.qld.gov.au website for up to date information on those eligible to travel, those who must obtain a border declaration pass, those who must quarantine and those ineligible to cross the border.

  • This border control point is accessible via a coded lock
  • Declaration pass holders must call Thargominda Police Station (07 4655 3200) to obtain the code
  • Pass holders can call 8am-5pm but should call in advance due to a lack of mobile phone reception at the border control point

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - Royal National Park -  Christmas & New Year holiday period - ROYAL NATIONAL PARK Princes Hwy at McKell Ave and Farnell Ave
properties.otherAdvice:
The Royal National Park is expected to be busy over the Christmas and New Year holiday period from Friday 25 to Monday 28 December and on New Year's Day 1 January.

Road closures will be in place as precincts and car parks reach capacity including Wattamolla Beach, Garie Beach, Audley, Maianbar and Bundeena.

When parking capacity is reached across all precincts, traffic will only be permitted to travel through the park. If there are significant delays, both the northern and southern entries to the park via Farnell Ave in Loftus and via Lady Wakehurst Dr in Otford will close. Entry will be maintained via McKell Ave in Waterfall for residents only. 

Visitors are encouraged to check the Royal National Park local alerts before travelling for updates on precinct access.

Road closures when precincts reach capacity:

  • Wattamolla Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Wattamolla Beach 
  • Garie Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Garie Beach
  • Maianbar Rd between Bundeena Dr and Maianbar township
  • Bundeena Dr between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Bundeena township

Traffic controllers and NSW Police will be on site managing access for local residents on Maianbar Rd and Bundeena Dr upon proof of residential address.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - Georges River National Park - Christmas & New Year holiday period - PICNIC POINT Henry Lawson Dr at The River Rd
properties.otherAdvice:
The Morgans Creek boat ramp precinct in Georges River National Park is expected to be busy over the Christmas and New Year holiday period from Friday 25 to Monday 28 December and on New Year's Day 1 January.

Once the precinct and carpark reaches capacity the entry via Burrawang Reach Rd opposite The River Rd at Henry Lawson Drive will be closed. After such time traffic will only be permitted to pass by on Henry Lawson Drive.

Visitors are encouraged to check Georges River National Park local alerts before travelling for updates on precinct access.

Traffic controllers and NPWS staff will be on site enforcing closures and directing motorists.
